  "name": "stUSDS Leverage Loop (Morpho Blue)",
  "description": "Execute one iteration of the stUSDS leverage loop on the Morpho Blue stUSDS/USDS market (Ethereum mainnet). Deposits USDS into the stUSDS vault (~16.8% APY), supplies stUSDS as collateral to Morpho, and borrows USDS against it. Each iteration increases leverage. At 2x leverage: ~29.5% net APY. Formula: Net APY = (stUSDS_Rate * leverage) - (Borrow_Rate * (leverage - 1)).\n\nRISK WARNINGS:\n1. stUSDS slashing risk -- stUSDS has a cut() function. If SKY-backed borrowers default, stUSDS holders get slashed.\n2. Variable borrow rate -- Morpho AdaptiveCurveIRM raises rates exponentially above 90% utilization.\n3. Liquidation risk -- At 2x leverage with 86% LLTV, a 42% stUSDS price drop triggers liquidation.\n4. Oracle risk -- MorphoChainlinkOracleV2 uses ERC-4626 share conversion plus Chainlink feeds.\n5. Correlated-pair risk -- stETH June 2022 precedent shows leverage loops can cascade during depegs.",
